The paper proposes an approach to internalize the stochasticity of renewable distributed energy resources (DERs) and risk tolerance of the distribution system operator in DLMP computations. This involves applying conic duality to a chance-constrained AC optimal power flow. The paper also discusses the design of a distribution electricity market. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis, design, and control of complex systems. The other likely sub-categories are cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper involves optimization, equilibrium analysis, and software implementation.
